# Vibe Reading Project Rules

## Architecture
- CLI tools in `cli/` — Node.js/TypeScript, run via `npx tsx`
- Web viewer in `viewer/` — React + esbuild, no framework
- Extractors in `cli/extractors/` — Tree-sitter WASM for AST parsing
- Shared parser in `cli/extractors/parser.ts` — all extractors import from here
- Types in `cli/types.ts` (CLI) and `viewer/src/shared-types.ts` (viewer)

## Testing
- CLI tests: `cd cli && npx tsx ../test/test.ts` (70 assertions)
- Build viewer: `cd viewer && node build.mjs`
- Always run tests after changes to extractors, types, or analyze pipeline
- Fixture files in `test/fixture/src/` — keep small and focused

## Conventions
- Entity types: concept, flow, history, jump
- File analysis JSONs stored in `.vibe-reading/files/`
- Global data in `.vibe-reading/global/`
- Use `parseFile()` and `cleanupParser()` from `parser.ts` — never duplicate Tree-sitter init
- Viewer styles are inline CSS strings in component files (no CSS modules)
- Monaco loaded from CDN, not bundled

## CLI Tools
- `analyze.ts` — extract entities from source files
- `enrich.ts` — agent writes enriched descriptions
- `auto-enrich.ts` — batch enrich from JSDoc
- `harness.ts` — validate coverage and schema
- `stats.ts` — quick project stats overview
